    {{#> case/paragraphe title="The challenge" }}
        <p>When I joined H&M in 2018, a big overhaul of the H&M loyalty program was underway, aiming to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>increase engagement and member satisfaction.</li>
            <li>decrease calls to customer service.</li>
            <li>grow the membership base.</li>
        </ul>
    {{/case/paragraphe}}

    {{#> case/paragraphe title="My role" }}
        <p><strong>UX Designer</strong>, working on several "cases" with different teams (Business Solution Analysts, IT Architects, UI
            Designers, etc.).
        </p>
        <p>We were working in a waterfall environment, and when I joined H&M, discovery, requirements and analysis had already been completed.</p>

    {{/case/paragraphe}}

    {{#> case/paragraphe title="The process" }}

        <p>For each case, I started by getting to know
            my colleagues and familiarising myself with the work done previously. Then, the process was to:
            <ul>
            <li>design,</li>
            <li>discuss with tech and business experts,</li>
            <li>tweak,</li>
            <li>user test,</li>
            <li>repeat.</li>
        </ul></p><p>Below
        are two examples of cases I worked on.</p>
    {{/case/paragraphe}}


