        <h4>The problem: "Okay... How do I use this?"</h4>
        <p>Usage of rewards was low. Previous research had shown that:
            <ul>
            <li>users had no idea how to use their offers online,</li>
            <li>staff was spending a lot of time helping customers with rewards in stores.</li>
        </ul>
         So, it had been decided to re-design the Rewards page, and to explore how we might make
            the processes of redeeming rewards simpler.
        </ul>
        </p>
        <h4>Design, test, iterate</h4>
        <p><strong>The Rewards page</strong> was a big source of confusion and frustration for users: it had a clear button to use the offer in store, but only text about how to use it online.</p>
        <p>We wanted to explore having a button to use in store. But that potentially meant applying an offer before you start shopping, which is
        unusual. In the first rounds of user testing, participants were unsure what to expect when clicking the new button. I had to tweak the copy and the design
        of the confirmation message several times.</p>
