        <h4>The problem</h4>
        <p>In some markets, H&M was to start rolling out invoices through
            Klarna, replacing other invoices methods. My job was to find how to make that fit into the existing
            H&MxKlarna pages (containing the purchases made with the "Pay in XX days with Klarna" payment method), and to
            provide helpful reminders when time came to pay the invoices.
        </p>
        <h4>Finding and paying invoices</h4>
        <p>The biggest challenge was that a lot of information and actions had to fit into one page. My first idea was to provide 2 tabs:
        one for "Pay in XX days", and the other one for Monthly invoices. But after gaining more understanding
        of how those payment methods work, and conducting some user tests, I settled on another layout: one tab
        for what was still to pay (all payment methods), and another for what had already been paid.</p>
