        <h4>Notifications</h4>
        <p>It had been decided on the business side that H&M would send push notifications about invoices.
        It was an effort to be helpful to customers. But there was also
            potential to have a negative impact, which I tried to minimize.
        </p>
        <p>I proposed to allow customers to choose which type of notifications they would receive from H&M,
        so they would be more in control. But as complexity increased, that ended up being de-scoped, with a promise to look into
        it again as part of a wider project to limit communications to customers.</p>
        <p>Without a way to choose the type of notifications received, data suggested fewer users would turn on push notifications.
        So I focused on highlighting things to pay within the interface instead, for instance through badges and an inbox for personal
            communications in the My account pages.</p>

