{{#> case/paragraphe title="Results" }}
    <p>The re-design, along with heavy marketing campaigns and gradual launch in new countries led to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>1 million new members in the first month after launch, and a member base that had doubled after 9
            months.
        </li>
        <li>a reduction in the number of conversation with customers service. In the first month after launch,
            membership-related queries accounted for about 7% of contacts, down from 9%.
        </li>
        <li>an increase of 14% in the part of members using rewards every time they shop.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>One disappointment was that
        we observed no increase in the perceived usefulness or relevance of rewards.
        Part of the problem is that a lot of "Rewards" are actually news and not offers:
        the template is used in ways I had not foreseen. This could have been avoided with better
        communication with Loyalty managers and content creators.
        </p>
